# Rental Items API Documentation

## Base Path

```
/api
```

---

## 1. Create a New Rental Item

- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/rentals`
- **Description:** Create a new rental item.
- **Request Body:**
  ```json
  {
    "name": "Professional Camera",
    "description": "Canon EOS R5 professional camera, suitable for photography enthusiasts",
    "categoryId": 1,
    "rentalRate": "200.00",
    "rentalPeriod": "daily",
    "deposit": "1000.00",
    "status": "available",
    "imageUrl": "https://example.com/images/camera.jpg"
  }
  ```
- **Response:**
  - `201 Created`  
    Returns the created rental item object.
  - `400 Bad Request`  
    Invalid input data.
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 2. Get All Rental Items

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/rentals`
- **Description:** Retrieve a list of all rental items with optional filters.
- **Query Parameters:**
  - `status` (optional): Filter by status (`available`, `rented_out`, `in_maintenance`)
  - `categoryId` (optional): Filter by category ID
  - `search` (optional): Search in name and description
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns an array of rental item objects.
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 3. Get Available Rental Items

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/rentals/available`
- **Description:** Retrieve a list of all available rental items.
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns an array of available rental item objects.
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 4. Get Rental Items by Category

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/rentals/category/{categoryId}`
- **Description:** Retrieve rental items by category ID.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `categoryId` (integer, required): Category ID
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns an array of rental item objects in the category.
  - `400 Bad Request`  
    Invalid category ID.
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 5. Get Rental Item by ID

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/rentals/{id}`
- **Description:** Retrieve details of a specific rental item by its ID.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Rental item ID
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns the rental item object.
  - `400 Bad Request`  
    Invalid item ID.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 6. Update a Rental Item

- **Endpoint:** `PUT /api/rentals/{id}`
- **Description:** Update an existing rental item.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Rental item ID
- **Request Body:** (any of the following fields)
  ```json
  {
    "name": "Updated Name",
    "description": "Updated description",
    "categoryId": 2,
    "rentalRate": "250.00",
    "rentalPeriod": "weekly",
    "deposit": "1200.00",
    "status": "available",
    "imageUrl": "https://example.com/images/updated.jpg"
  }
  ```
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns the updated rental item object.
  - `400 Bad Request`  
    Invalid input data or item ID.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 7. Delete a Rental Item

- **Endpoint:** `DELETE /api/rentals/{id}`
- **Description:** Delete a rental item by its ID.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Rental item ID
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns a success message.
  - `400 Bad Request`  
    Invalid item ID.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 8. Update Rental Item Status

- **Endpoint:** `PUT /api/rentals/{id}/status`
- **Description:** Update the status of a rental item.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Rental item ID
- **Request Body:**
  ```json
  {
    "status": "rented_out"
  }
  ```
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns the updated rental item object.
  - `400 Bad Request`  
    Invalid status value or item ID.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

